# High-Protein Chicken, Broccoli & Sweet Potato Bowl

## Macros (per serving)
- **Protein:** 42g
- **Carbs:** 38g
- **Fat:** 14g
- **Calories:** ~450

---

## Ingredients (2 servings)

| Component | Amount |
|-----------|--------|
| Chicken breast | 12 oz (340g) |
| Sweet potatoes | 2 medium (400g) |
| Broccoli florets | 3 cups (270g) |
| Olive oil | 2 tbsp |
| Garlic | 4 cloves |
| Lemon juice | 1 tbsp |
| Smoked paprika | 1 tsp |
| Salt & pepper | To taste |

---

## Instructions

### 1. Roast the Sweet Potatoes
- Preheat oven to **425°F (220°C)**
- Cube sweet potatoes into ½-inch pieces
- Toss with 1 tbsp olive oil, paprika, salt, pepper
- Roast **25–30 minutes** until caramelized

### 2. Sear the Chicken
- Pound chicken to even thickness
- Season with salt, pepper, half the garlic
- Sear in remaining oil **6–7 min/side** until 165°F internal
- Rest 5 minutes, then slice

### 3. Sauté the Broccoli
- Steam or sauté with remaining garlic **4–5 minutes**
- Keep bright green with slight crunch
- Finish with lemon juice

---

## Assembly Tips

- **Boost protein:** Add 2 tbsp hemp seeds (+6g protein)
- **Meal prep:** Stores 4 days refrigerated
- **Flavor upgrade:** Tahini drizzle or hot sauce

Want a sheet-pan version for easier cleanup?
